Unlike some of the other data integration models, <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Objects</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) don't stop at data abstraction. The <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Objects</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) framework also incorporates a good number of J2EE patterns and best practices. <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Objects</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) support a disconnected programming model. The <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Object</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) programming model prescribes patterns of usage that allow clean separation of each of these concerns.
<br><br>
Put simply, <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Objects</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) is a framework for data application development, which includes an architecture and API. <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Objects</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) simplify the J2EE data programming model. <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Objects</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) abstracts data in a service oriented architecture (SOA). <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Objects</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) unify data application development. <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Objects</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) support and integrate XML. <a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">Service Data Objects</a> (<a href="../../../tools/emf/scripts/sdo.php" label="Service Data Object (SDO)" id="Service Data Object (SDO)">SDO</a>) incorporate J2EE patterns and best practices.
<br><br>
